President Muhammadu Buhari, yesterday on behalf of the Federal Executive Council and all Nigerians sent warm greetings to a renowned Mathematician and Economist, Prof Chukwuka Okonjo, the Obi of Ogwashiukwu, on his 90th birthday. The nonagenarian is the father of a former Minister of Finance, Mrs Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala. Buhari, in a statement by his spokesman Femi Adesina, joins Ogwashiukwu community in Delta State, immediate and extended Okonjo family; professional colleagues and friends, in celebrating the cerebral scholar whose imprint on education in Nigeria and beyond remains indelible. President Buhari prays that the Almighty God will grant the Obi of Ogwashiukwu longer life, more strength and good health to keep serving humanity.